collections.name: NOVEL ENCRYPTION (2015) BY KEVIN ABOSCH
collections.description: NOVEL ENCRYPTION are 6 GAN works created by Kevin Abosch in 2015 for the occasion of SIME Miami.  Working with the MNIST dataset of handwritten digits as the starting point for a series of "novel encryptions" generated  using a convolutional neural network (CNN) but stopping the training early, resulting in digits of varying decipherability.  Each work presents a grid of four glyphs.  Across the six works there are 24 glyphs which the artist uses as the foundation of a cipher alphabet.

collections.name: EARLY EPOCHS (2017) BY KEVIN ABOSCH
collections.description: Kevin Abosch’s 2017 project, EARLY EPOCHS, is a key contribution to the conversation between human creativity & AI. In this work, Abosch employs Progressive GAN (PGAN) technology to explore both the algorithms behind image generation & the underlying data that informs them. By training the PGAN on a personal archive of mobile phone photos, the artist encourages us to reflect on the often subtle connection between our everyday experiences and the digital data that is increasingly shaping our cultural landscape. Each of the 30 works in the series is composed of a grid of four images, captured from the nascent stages of the GAN’s learning process - its early epochs. Here, before the network has had the opportunity to refine and settle into a coherent, detailed representation, the raw, abstract outputs reveal a visual form of "surface truth." These images encapsulate an ephemeral quality: an arresting, colorful abstraction that resists the urge to become immediately figurative or literal.

collections.name: Cycles by Material Protocol Arts
collections.description: Cycles by Material Protocol Arts is a network sculpture composed of space and time, a meditation on recurrence and change. As a protocol artwork, Cycles explores the unique affordances of live running computer programs as art objects.

In the distant future, humanity has ventured beyond the confines of Earth, exploring planets adorned with colors and life unknown to human eyes. On one such purple planet, an astronaut rides his celestial chariot, drawn by a mythical white horse said to be blessed by the Ethereum Moon. The moon, a beacon of decentralized hope, has become the guiding light for explorers seeking unity between man, nature, and technology.

Legends tell of the "Chariot of Lumina," a relic said to bring balance to the forces of creation and destruction. The gears of the chariot symbolize humanity’s relentless ingenuity, while the horse represents the untamed spirit of the cosmos. Together, they traverse the alien landscape, charting a path for those who dream of boundless frontiers.
